shared_text:
Cranston, RI Police Department
January 9 at 10:42 AM ·

Good morning Cranston!!

We would like to give a big thank you to Chris Herren and Herren Talks for coming to speak to the community last night! The Cranston East auditorium was left with standing room only! We would also like to thank everyone that came tonight and all those that helped make this possible. The message Chris brings is an important one and we are glad it got to reach so many.

The State Opioid Response grant is funded by the RI Department of Behavioral Healthcare, Developmental Disabilities & Hospitals and the SPC Regional Prevention Coalition. This competitive grant was awarded to our department who partnered with the Cranston Substance Abuse Task Force to educate and bring awareness on the opioid epidemic to the community.

Thank you again and what a great night!

October 16, 2019 at 8:56 PM ·

Good evening Cranston...hazardous weather ahead!

The CPD urges caution over the next 12 hours as weather conditions are rapidly deteriorating. Expect heavy rain on our streets making travel difficult. The possibility of pooling of water and flooding on roadways in some areas exist so PLEASE take it slow. Additionally, heavy wind may cause power outages in the area. As always, please contact us if you need assistance...we will be on the roads all night!! STAY SAFE!!

post_text: Last night, we had the honor of acknowledging our local heroes. Thank you, Corporal Joseph Joel, US Army Yeoman 3rd Class Petty Officer Norman Heckler, US Army Electronics Mate 3rd Class Lou Kelly, US Navy Private 1st Class Raymond Ugone US Navy for your service and thank you Katrina French for all your hard work on behalf of our Veterans.

shared_text:
Cranston Parks and Recreation Department
August 20, 2019 at 3:03 PM ·

Thank you to everyone who made this summer fun and exciting, from parents who entrusted their children with us to the staff who spent their summer making an impact on the young people of Cranston.

Thank you to everyone who chose to spend those hot summer days at the Budlong Pool as well as the pool staff who kept it running seven days a week.

We now turn our attention to Fall and Winter. Look for upcoming announcements on Saturday Morning Basketball, Winter Tennis, Women's Fitness, Living Arts Acting Class, and Adult Pickleball. Once we have program details set, we will update our Facebook page and the Parks and Recreation website.
